<br>
July 3, 3180<br>
<br>
My Brother,<br>
<br>
I hope that time is treating you well. I write to you in the middle of a war zone on the moon. The Sambata Tribe in the Peaks of Dawnshroud have been in a state of uprising for some time now and the Dwarven King has sent me to aid in any way i can. There are usually up to 6 of us grouped together fighting them at one time, with few casualties as fortune would have it. The Tribes leader is somehow tied in with the Rockhoppers, a group of small odd looking creatures that will just as soon spit in your face and blind you before you can say StormGuard. <br>
<br>
Horrible things they are...<br>
<br>
I have been fortunate to have attained more spells whilst I have been here, which have aided us all greatly. Yesterday we had a deadly run in with the Tribal Advisor, a nasty Erudite who is aiding the Sambata in some way.  The political connection is beyond me, though I highly doubt the noble city of Erudin would have anything to do with these horrid cave dwellers, so the connection must lie within Paineel. That is where you come in. I am told that there may be a way to infiltrate Paineel to find this information out. I am not asking you to do it, but I am sure I heard you tell of someone you knew in Erudin, and that is what I am counting on. I am sending you this note with a young druid, and pray Brell finds it in your hands quickly.<br>
<br>
I know that you and I have never gotten on very well Zlevg, Mother and Father never treated you with as fair a hand as I thought you deserved, and I know that their passing at the hands of the goblins hit us both hard. I understand from speaking with Rasaella that you have taken to fighting the new goblin arrivals on the shores of our land. I am sorry to burden you with this task when you already have your hands full...<br>
<br>
There is more I must tell you. The Dark Circles are in a state of gathering. I have pledged to join them. The Sisters of the Rose no longer need us to Defend them as they are quite strong enough to do so on their own. I hope that you will understand as there is too much in this change to explain to you. Ah but you probably know all this allready. I offer you a place within the Circles my brother and hope to have you at my side once more.<br>
<br>
I hope that you are continuing your studies, being a warrior must not be an easy thing in these times. Stay strong and I hope to see you soon. I have instructed the druid to wait for your reply and have already paid him well for doing so. We must act quickly if we are to quell this uprising. I must get back to healing my party now. Stay safe, and may Brell guide us all...<br>
<br>
Gvelz <br>
